{
  "texts": [
    "Data-Adaptive Techniques.",
    "Our experiments evaluate the performance of various graph-building paradigms within our taxonomy (SS, NP, II, ND, and DC).",
    "While NP-based methods perform the worst overall and are the least scalable, there is no clear winner across all dataset sizes and query workloads.",
    "(1) Scalability: II-based approaches have superior efficiency during indexing and higher scalability in both querying and indexing.",
    "(2) Query Answering: ND-based methods have the best query performance overall."
  ]
}